<p>Because range of int in C/C++ is <code>-2147483648</code> to <code>+2147483647</code>. </p>

<p>So when you add <code>1</code>, it overflows the max limit of <code>int</code>. </p>

<p>For better understanding, assume the whole range of <code>int</code> puts on a circle in proper order:</p>

<pre><code>2147483647 + 1 == -2147483648

2147483647 + 2 == -2147483647
</code></pre>

<p>If you want to overcome this, try to use <code>long long</code> instead of <code>int</code>.</p>
